aad.description: AzureAD app's used by clusters for RBAC of users.

aks_prefix.description: AKS resource prefix as dictated by naming convention.

availability_zones.description: Availability zones for node pools, for example [1,2]

defaultpool_max_pods.description: Max pods per node in default pool.

defaultpool_scale.description: Number of worker nodes in default pool.

defaultpool_vm_size.description: VM type of worker nodes in default pool.

env_name.description:
Environment name is used a prefix for resources and as part of the domain name of services running in the clusters.
For example for name=cpe, env_name=k8ss the domain becomes: app.namespace.cpe.k8ss.example.com
Typically "k8s{data.azurerm_resource_group.env.tags[EnvironmentType]}"

name.description: Name of cluster, also used in domain name; app.namespace.<name>.env.subdomain.

node_pools.description:
List of additional node pools.
When max_scale > scale autoscaling is enabled.
Valid values for scale and max_scale are 1..100.

outbound_type.description: Network egress path. Valid values are 'userDefinedRouting' (default) or 'loadBalancer'

resource_group.description: The Resource Group that is used for creating resources.

route_table_id.description: Routing for all subnets containing Pods.

service_endpoints.description: Service endpoints provide direct connectivity to Azure services, for example [Microsoft.Sql]

sku.description: Support tier. Valid values are 'Free' (default) or 'Paid'.

subnet_newbits.description:
Subnet newbits is the number of bits to add to the VNet address mask to produce the subnet mask.
For example given a /16 VNet and subnet_newbits=4 would result in /20 subnets.
Note: this values must be the same for all subnets in the vnet.

subnet_num.description: Subnet index of vnet that is used by this cluster. Valid from 1 to (2^subnet_newbits)-1

tags.description: Azure resource tags to comply with organisation policy.

vnet.description: VNet in which AKS clusters get a subnet.
